Karaikal port is a lagoon type harbour which is connected to sea by 10400mtrs long/160 mtrs wide outer approach channel. Harbour basin is well protected by 2 crescent shaped breakwaters of 600mtrs length. The breakwater extends in an easterly direction from the shore one each on North and South of approach channel. Length of inner approach channel will be 600 mtrs connected to Turning Circle  (Dia:500 mtrs). TC will have a 220mtrs opening at the southern end and tapering to 180mtrs defining 460mtrs long berth front (2 berths). Import cargo include: liquid Cargo, Coal, Coke Timber, General Cargo and export cargo will be Construction material, Clinker, Machineries etc.

Kattupalli port operated by the Port division of L&T Shipbuilding Ltd. is a lagoon typeharbour protected by two breakwaters with a 2.2 Km long/165 mtrs wide outer approach channel and an inner approach channel1.5 Km long with a Turning Circle of Diameter 570 mtrs. The Channel and berth depth is maintained at 14m. The Port has in Phase I two Container Berths and a Container yard. It is equipped with state of the art equipment including 6 Quay Cranes and 15 RTGC’s and has initial annual capacity of 1.2 million TEUs. A CFS is also available within the Complex with a closed warehouse. Apart from Container Cargo the Port is likely to handle Project/ Break Bulk and Ro Ro Cargo. The Port harbour also has a Shipyard and a Modular Fabrication Facility
The port consists of: 1) Outer anchorage 2) Jetties : 20 meter in length for Roll-on-Roll off and adjoining 30 meter in length for load on load off.

The port is equipped with 55 berths. An offshore berth at Pir Pau also handles liquefied gas and some the POL traffic and liquid chemicals. the anchorage area is vsst extending over 20 NM outside the harbour. Lighterage operations are carried out outside port limits at the custom notified area. The passenger ship terminal is located at the Southern most tip of the port which is adjacent to the Naval facility. The entrance to this is through the GREEN GATE. The terminal here is also used for docking of other cargo ships when the passenger ships are not berthing. Part of the building is lused as a cargo shed for the cargo brought by the cargo vessels but only when the passenger ship is not expected. The Port has got a impounded dock called the Indira Dock with a depth maintained between 8 to 9 meter. The dock has got a lock gate. There are 23 berths in Indira Dock handling containers, general cargo, like fertilizer and foodgrains and heavy lifts. There are semi-tidal docks namely the Victoria and Prince's Dock. Dock has 14 multi-purpose berths. Prince's Dock has 8 multi-purpose berth. The gates are being used during window period of 3 hours before high tide till high tide time. The lock structure is of stone masonry. Presently the Prince's dock is being used as a tidal dock.
